Trade unionists and politicians who failed in the August 8 election are among 99 people who have been shortlisted for chief officer jobs in Kisii county. According to the list published in the county website, five people, Augustine Miencha, Charles Nyangeri, Joseph Chacha, Mauline Moenga and Patrick Lumumba, were shortlisted for the county secretary position. Knut Kisii South branch executive secretary Geoffrey Mogire has been shortlisted in the department of Administration, Enforcement and Devolved Units.  Mogire, a human rights defender, initially wanted to become the county assembly speaker, but was prevailed upon to step down for David Kombo. Kuppet county chairman Osoro Okondo and his secretary Omari Otungu have also been shortlisted.